BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Bank Lending, Bradesco, Redecard Earnings

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-04-27T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/brazil-daybook-bank-lending-bradesco-redecard-earnings.html
Brazil central bank releases
lending figures for the month of March. Credit growth picked up
in February in spite of higher lending rates. Government
officials are trying to slow lending growth to contain the
fastest inflation in 29 months.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Tulio Maciel, head of the central bank’s economic department,
speaks to reporters about lending figures for the month of March
at 11 a.m.
*Bradesco holds conference call with journalists on first-
quarter earnings at 11 a.m.
*Eletronuclear Chief Executive Officer Othon Luiz Pinheiro da
Silva speaks to reporters in  Rio de Janeiro  about nuclear energy
after the Japan tsunami. Eletronuclear is a unit of Eletrobras.
12:30 p.m.
*Acucar Guarani’s seminar in Sao Paulo on the sugar and ethanol
industry, with the company’s top management and consultants,
starting at 8:30 a.m.  EARNINGS:
*Bradesco (BBDC4 BZ), bef. mkt.
*Natura (NATU3 BZ), aft. mkt.
*Redecard (RDCD3 BZ), aft. mkt.  ECONOMY:
*Fipe weekly Sao Paulo CPI at 5 a.m.
*Bank lending at 10:30 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*M. Dias Branco (MDIA3 BZ) bought Pilar for 69.9 million reais
*Marfrig (MRFG3 BZ) plans to sell $500 million of debt due 2018,
Fitch said
*Embraer (EMBR3 BZ) reaffirmed 2011 sales forecast  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 0.3 percent to 67,144.26.
*The real rose 0.4 percent to 1.5621 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
